1. Have a mage summon mod rods for ALL the casters incase of emergency.<br>
2. Have EVERYONE standing, NOBODY sitting.<br>
3. Have wizards/nukers start nuking fay when he is at 60%.<br>
4. Have ALL druids be back up healers and buffers.<br>
5. Have EVERYONE VERY resisted.<br>
7. Have tanks near the shore at the South part of the beach.<br>
8. Have the casters BEHIND the tanks  near the SW part to Set up at.<br>
9. Have NO ONE sitting until after 30 seconds of spawn. <br>
10. Don't Send in pets till 80%.  <br>
<br>
Heh hope this helped everyone :) now I need some suggestions if there are anymore plz :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/15/01 8:40:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> Have 4 crap buffs up on everyone before you start casting buffs and resists<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueiladwen123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiladwen123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/15/01 11:39:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> Make sure the real Fay isnt up...if you dont and he is..well damnit your in my world of bad luck..unless your guild is uber and not slow like mine /grin :) <p><b><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=85718>Eiladwen Treebarker</a></b> <BR> <b><i>Karana Server - Lightbringers</b></i> <BR> <b><i>57th Preserver of Tunare</b></i>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubetina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>betina</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/16/01 12:18:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~mhuang/eq/pics/betina-new.gif height=120 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> Get dummy buffs on, and remember that Faydedar is basically Nagafen. Stick to those tactics and you should be ok.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umashesta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mashesta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/16/01 2:27:33 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> We have done fay quite a few times...hehe i think 3 last week. The following are some of the things we do...<br>
<br>
1. 4 dummy buffs as the first buffs on everyone<br>
2. have tanks on beach next to the dorf casters behind them near the rock wall<br>
3. Pets are ok right away<br>
4. If you have enough clerics do a group with 2 clerics 4 melee... if not just try to get highest level tanks with clerics...our last killing we only had 2 clerics total hehe<br>
5. Have healers /assist fay and help heal whoever is taking the beating<br>
6. I think we usuealy start nukeing at 40% and druids with the frost spell can really add up some damage, i think 80% of the time I cast frost i hit for full on fay<br>
7. for resists, try to make sure everyone has at least 90 base MR to resist the fear, as much FR and MR as possible is better<br>
<br>
Sorry for sloppy list, just trying to offer some quick advice in my morning stupper (hour 8 of a 12 hour shift hehe)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubraidfreak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>braidfreak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/16/01 8:04:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> things like jboots, goblin skull earring, and other instant cast items really help out with MOBs that debuff.  also, memming a quick spell like see invis works great too.  just make sure you keep them in your first few buff slots...when you get dispelled, it's almost always one of the first 2 or 3 slots that gets debuffed.  then just insta click or cast that fast crap buff again to save from having your good buffs dispelled.<br>
<br>
druids, if there's no mages, make sure you thorn up the few main tanks.  those damage sheilds are cheap mana and really add up on long fights.  also, if you have chloroblast (not chloroplast), make sure you have it memmed.  it heals a good deal and is very fast.  your job is to keep those tanks alive until the CHeals land.  don't nuke until the end when things are almost over.  your job is backup healer, not wizard. <p><img src=http://braidfreak.homestead.com/Files/mylogo.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/01 6:29:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> We had all standing but the main tank that sat down next to me when I turned in the pod. Faydedar went right for him :) No deaths, easy dragon. <p><p><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/18/01 7:09:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> I personally have very little dragon experience at this point.  I know it is in these boards somewhere, but I would rather just hear it fresh if anyone is willing.  I am down to needing Faydedar to finish up my epic.  My guild can only put up around two groups in the 50-57 range, more on the lower end of that range than the upper.  I am trying to gather up the masses to assist us with this fight, but I was curious about how many might be needed and what is a good class/lvl allotment for this fight?<br>
<br>
 <p>-Galipure Stormdancer<BR>Sun Clan of Warriors<BR>Solusek Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umashesta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mashesta</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/18/01 8:02:45 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar Suggestions ?</span><hr size=1> Make sure everyone has resist gear before ya try and then just give it a go. I'd recomend for first attempts to have between 24-36 people. Ya, may be overkill but will make learning process a bit easier. I'd say 24 is ideal for Fay though 12 people that know what they are doing could pull it off I am sure.<br>
